[realms]
; realm boundaries FOLLOW features (#81): between two vertices, `along`
; traces the feature's curve - the ridge IS the border, and moving it
; moves the border with it
; coastal edges follow the coastlines themselves - a nation ends at the
; sea's actual curve, not at a straight line near it
realm "Valemark" : area (110,240) along westspine along westshore (552,540) (350,530) (160,600) along farwest (100,320)
realm "Carrowen" : area (160,600) (350,530) (552,540) along westshore (520,990) (115,990) along farwest (110,850)
